## Stack
GitHub Copilot agent mode in VS Code is the primary harness on Windows. Claude Code CLI also works — the `.claude/` files in this repo (`.claude/agents/`, `.claude/skills/`, `CLAUDE.md`) are read by both harnesses. Per-harness config lives in `.vscode/settings.json` (Copilot terminal allow-list) and `.claude/settings.json` if present (Claude Code hooks/permissions). PowerShell default shell (CI may run PS 5.1; local is PS 7). For capability details (skills, instructions files, MCP, memory, subagents), check the official docs - [code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot) for Copilot agent mode or [code.claude.com/docs](https://code.claude.com/docs/) for Claude Code CLI - they're always current.

